name: Low Cadence, Reloaded #1
description:
You are revisiting a session from the Early Base Phase with a twist. Low Cadence efforts to simulate the climbs and finish, including some 1-minute efforts at your Maximal Aerobic Power (MAP). 



It is good to maintain some intensity during the early phases of a training plan; This can help to prolong the endurance effects of the training and keep the high-intensity efforts familiar.
